  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Urdu compound word \u201cghairat-e-ashiq\u201d?",
  "response": "The Urdu compound word \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" can be translated to \"honor of the lover\" or \"pride of the lover\" in English. In Urdu poetry and literature, \"ghairat\" refers to honor, pride, or self-respect, while \"ashiq\" means lover. Therefore, \"ghairat-e-ashiq\" typically refers to the sense of pride, dignity, or honor that a lover feels or upholds in matters of love and relationships.",
